article.headline: Kent St. 93, Shawnee St. 42
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Al Fisher scored 16 points to lead Kent State's offensive drive as they routed Shawnee State, 93-42, at the M.A.C. Center on Tuesday. Six players scored in the double-digits for Kent State (6-6), which never trailed in the game and led by a towering 53 points with 39 seconds left. At halftime, Kent State led 53-16. Tyree Evans had 12 points, Anthony Simpson came off the bench to add 12, and Julian Sullinger and Brandon Parks had 10 points each for Kent State. Frank Henry-Ala also came off the bench to score 10 for the Golden Flashes. Shawnee State (5-8) shot just 33.3 percent on field goals and 30.8 percent on 3-pointers. Justin Patrick was Shawnee State's leading scorer with nine points.
